transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra.

Speaker 2: This is Joanna speaking.

Speaker 1: How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I had prescribed to get something from you guys a while back.

Speaker 1: And I don't know, it must be you do automatic send out or something?

Speaker 2: Well, it depends.

Speaker 1: So we're not a subscription.

Speaker 2: You can set up your account however you want.

Speaker 1: Let me access your account so I can better assist you.

Speaker 2: Can I get your name and date of birth?

Speaker 1: James Parker, P-A-R-K-E-R, 9-14-57.

Speaker 2: Okay, thanks, Mr. Parker.

Speaker 1: I have your account pulled up.

Speaker 2: So it looks like currently you're set up to receive refills every three months.

Speaker 1: Now, as a VIP status customer, of course, you can modify the quantity and frequency of your orders at any time or put a pause on your account.

Speaker 2: So you are getting 40.

Speaker 1: You can always reduce that to 25 or 10, which, of course, would lower the cost.

Speaker 2: And you can delay your order or space out the frequency or put a pause on your account.

Speaker 1: That way you can retain your VIP pricing and still have access to your prescription because otherwise canceling it would cancel any available future refills.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I guess if it's every three months, that's probably good.

Speaker 2: You want to reduce the quantity, perhaps?

Speaker 1: You'd be getting 40 every three months.

Speaker 2: And if you ever say that there's one month where you don't need it quite yet, you can call us.

Speaker 1: What's the difference in cost between, like, 40 and 25?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So 40 of them you're getting for $163.95.

Speaker 2: 25 would be $113.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I thought probably 25 would be good for me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So update your future order to 25.

Speaker 1: And then did you want me to keep it on a three-month reoccurring?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Excellent.

Speaker 1: So I've gone ahead and updated that.

Speaker 2: And like I said, if you ever want to modify that or delay an order or say you want to order more before your next refill date, just give us a call and let us know.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: That sounds awesome.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Well, thank you for being a VIP status questioner.

Speaker 1: I'm glad I was able to help.

Speaker 2: Well, thank you very much.

Speaker 1: You've done just what I needed to do.

Speaker 2: Usually it seems like it's always more problems than this.

Speaker 1: It's like, man, I got through to you guys right away and boom, boom, boom.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So it was perfect.

Speaker 2: Oh, I'm so happy to hear that.

Speaker 1: Thanks, Mr. Parker.

Speaker 2: Have a great rest of your day.

Speaker 1: You have a super day, too.

Speaker 2: Take care.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
